    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong>, <strong>sliced garlic </strong>and<strong> </strong>100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[175ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>thyme</strong> (chuck it in, stalks and all!) and cook, covered, for 8-10 min or until the onion has completely softened, stirring frequently</p>",
