    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>, then add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Gradually whisk 100ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[175ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> and the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong> into the roux, and cook for 4-5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains, then stir through <strong>half</strong> the <strong>grated cheese </strong>(save the rest for later!) with your<strong> clotted cream </strong>– this is your <strong>cheese sauce</strong></p>",
